commit.message: Update README.md
Update README.md
slight modification to installation instructions
Added readme with demo gif
Update sample audio clips to actual ones.
Update initial DB points to point to new S3 bucket.
Push the new sandbox.
Change S2 bucket name to storyteller-demo
Show an alert on the filmed view saying that it's not yet supported.
Lower ios version requirement to 8.0
Update configurations.plist to the new sandbox.
Remove all credentials during logout for good measure.
Remove the old alertview used to create new storypoints.
Add a custom view for new storypoints that uses a map snapshot to show where the new storypoint will be.

Add the start of a possible custom add story point view.

Additionally add gesture recognizes to the spoken / filmed story views so that the keyboard can be dismissed.
Add an activity indicator to the stories view. On LTE, it can take some times to get the stories so having feedback is good.
Add a sample filmed story to the nearby points demo knobs.
Remove written stories. In order to get back to written stories, this commit should have all the required changes.
Add various comments to StoryTableViewCell.
Cleanup of the stories view controller.
Comment updates.

Remove the requestLocation function from LocationManager. According to Apple documentation, it requests the user location once and then disables location services, which is not desired for this app.

Several places were relying on using requestLocation() calls to hopefully get a location fix faster, but in its absence now... simply wait until the location comes in.
Only allow the admin user to populate the initial database.
Remove unused image files.
Modify the app name from using the target name by default ('storyteller-ios') to StoryTeller. Also remove some unneeded png files.
Updates to Assets.xcassets for microphone and films images.
Add app icons in the various required sizes.
Add several sample channels / messages.
Setup the demo nearby storypoints to be spoken stories.
Make sure to add newly created storypoints to the top of table instead of appending to the bottom.
